      <hedline>
        <hl1>Bluestocking Blues</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Ina Jaffe letter on Judith Shulevitz's September 10 article questions why Pres Bill Clinton, following John F Kennedy's example with his brother, did not appoint Hillary Clinton attorney general (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>John F. Kennedy, whom Bill Clinton greatly admired, was not dissuaded by the charge of nepotism from appointing his brother attorney general. One wonders why Clinton did not name his wife to that post, rather than let her lurk around the fringes of the administration attempting to push her agendas without the accountability that would come with a formal position.</p>
        <p>Ina Jaffe  Hamden, Conn.</p>
      </block>
